parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel tank rust and leakage can cause fuel to spill onto the ground, creating a fire hazard and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.

fuel pumps out of the gas cap at a high rate

fuel blows out of the gas cap when loosened.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank selector valve can cause fuel to leak onto the ground, creating a fire hazard and potentially leading to a vehicle fire or explosion.
symptoms: Fuel leaks from the rear fuel tank
fuel spills onto the ground
fuel tank overflows
fuel smell in the garage or driveway
fuel running out of the tank onto the driveway.
